import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['US_Gross'] = data['US_Gross'].astype(float)
    data['Worldwide_Gross'] = data['Worldwide_Gross'].astype(float)
    plt.scatter(data['US_Gross'], data['Worldwide_Gross'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?')
    plt.xlabel('US Gross')
    plt.ylabel('Worldwide Gross')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Production_Budget'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Production_Budget'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Production_Budget'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['Production_Budget'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['Production_Budget'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["Production_Budget"].median():,.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['Production_Budget'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Mean: {data["Production_Budget"].mean():,.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Production Budget')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Production_Budget?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['IMDB_Rating'] = pd.to_numeric(data['IMDB_Rating'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['IMDB_Rating'].dropna(), vert=False, showfliers=True, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), medianprops=dict(color='black'), whiskerprops=dict(color='black'), capprops=dict(color='black'))
    ax.set_xlabel('IMDB Rating')
    ax.set_yticklabels(['IMDB Rating'])
    ax.axvline(data['IMDB_Rating'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['IMDB_Rating'].median()))
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of IMDB_Rating?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
